title: 820-00165 wont boot
message:
Arrived with liquid damage and the fan spinning fast the second it was powered on.

U8130 and R8133 were replaced along with U5110 and R5125. After replacement no change still fast fan second it was powered on with no light.

After replacing the SMC, fan spins normal now light is back but turns off after a few seconds, then turns back on with no usb activity or chime. During the first fan spin draws around 336 ma. When it turns back on draws the normal amperage is drawn around 550-600ma

Tried known good bios with no change.

Sound like bad CPU from U8130 and R8133 being hit with liquid? If not what should be checked next??

Also heated CPU with good flux

title: 820-00165 wont boot
message:
Check all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and traces.
Clean/remove J6100.

title: 820-00165 wont boot
message:
all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and traces  are good

J6100 removed

no change
